title: Extended Hotline Quick Guide
text: Q: POS is locked in the middle of a card payment (Pop up blocks with fx. “Rejected “” not approved “” wrong pin " message) A: Log in to the POS on Teamviewer and press ALT+F4 (this shortcut is disabled on the customer's keyboard so it must be done through TV.) press " no " in the box if the purchase has gone through. The customer can now try again. Q: POS application is shut down and will not start A: open the "Task Manager/Task Manager” and exit the processes “DdDPOS.net“, and" POSupdate.exe” Q: The item scanner does not work, the red light does not appear when you press the button A: either unplug the USB port for 30 seconds. Or turn off the pc completely for 30 seconds. Q: Receipt printer does not print receipts. A: check if there is light in it, if not, then there is a power button on the front, if it is on, then check that there are all three cables in the back. Q: Message “cannot start DdDPOS” A: check the SQL Server if it is in single user or suspect mode. Start query on the affected database, copy / paste below with the database name. Click Execute. ALTER DATABASE ' name’ SET MULTI_USER; GO It is also possible that it has thrown the config. Use this guide on how to fix it: POS - won't start - POSCONFIG is empty Q: PC hangs A: Restart or shut down, wait a moment, then switch on again Q: Missing PW for PC A: The password in general is: justenter and user is User, unless they have added their own pw/user. Then they’re on their own. Q: Can’t log into BO A: Usually it means they’ve shut down the browser without logging out, which means they’re still logged in. Use this guide to logout user: Logout user Q: They don't know Client ID and PW + Machine login and PW A: You can look it up in the DdD Backoffice Support Tools Client information -> search client->show client These things are in theory not the part of extended support Wrong prices Status Putting goods in stock Label printer / A4 printer problems
description:
Q: POS is locked in the middle of a card payment 

(Pop up blocks with fx. “Rejected “” not approved “” wrong pin " message) 

A: Log in to the POS on Teamviewer and press ALT+F4 (this shortcut is disabled on the customer's keyboard so it must be done through TV.) press " no " in the box if the purchase has gone through. The customer can now try again. 

  

Q: POS application is shut down and will not start 

A: open the "Task Manager/Task Manager” and exit the processes “DdDPOS.net“, and" POSupdate.exe” 

  

Q: The item scanner does not work, the red light does not appear when you press the button 

A: either unplug the USB port for 30 seconds. Or turn off the pc completely for 30 seconds.  

  

Q: Receipt printer does not print receipts. 

A: check if there is light in it, if not, then there is a power button on the front, if it is on, then check that there are all three cables in the back. 

  

Q: Message “cannot start DdDPOS” 

A: check the SQL Server if it is in single user or suspect mode. 
  

Start query on the affected database, copy / paste below with the database name. Click Execute. 

ALTER DATABASE ' name’ 

SET MULTI_USER; 

GO 

  

It is also possible that it has thrown the config. Use this guide on how to fix it: 

POS - won't start - POSCONFIG is empty


 Q: PC hangs

 A: Restart or shut down, wait a moment, then switch on again 


Q: Missing PW for PC 

A: The password in general is: justenter and user is User, unless they have added their own pw/user. Then they’re on their own. 


Q: Can’t log into BO 

A: Usually it means they’ve shut down the browser without logging out, which means they’re still logged in. Use this guide to logout user: Logout user 


Q: They don't know Client ID and PW + Machine login and PW 

A: You can look it up in the DdD Backoffice Support Tools 

Client information -> search client->show client


  

  

These things are in theory not the part of extended support
